text: Fyfield is a village located in North-West Hampshire, England. The nearest town is Andover. The village is close to the villages of: Thruxton, Kimpton and Appleshaw. The village church is St Nicholas' Church of Fyfield. The village has a rough population of 440 people (according to the 2011 census). Part of Redenham Park is in Fyfield. == References == == Other websites == * Fyfield in the Victoria County History of Hampshire Category:Villages in Hampshire
